{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim_docker/pullrequests/1/comments/33409602.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/srcsim_docker/diff/osrf/srcsim_docker:fc0a09175e7b..ea3767cfaf6e?path=docker%2Frun_container.bash"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim_docker/pull-requests/1/_/diff#comment-33409602"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim_docker/pullrequests/1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim_docker/pull-requests/1"}}, "title": "Initial SRC cloudsim gazebo docker container"}, "content": {"raw": "I added my user account to the `docker` group so I don't have to use `sudo` ([docker docs](https://docs.docker.com/engine/installation/linux/linux-postinstall/)). Perhaps we could make this a non-sudo command? People could still invoke this script with sudo if they don't want to modify the user groups.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I added my user account to the <code>docker</code> group so I don't have to use <code>sudo</code> (<a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://docs.docker.com/engine/installation/linux/linux-postinstall/\" rel=\"nofollow\">docker docs</a>). Perhaps we could make this a non-sudo command? People could still invoke this script with sudo if they don't want to modify the user groups.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-03-17T22:00:48.429947+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c